    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just weird how you say \"there's no evidence\" but then immediately explain how they use machine learning for pattern recognition... if they can use wi-fi to track my location and usage analytics to know my schedule, why wouldn't they be able to cross-reference that with other data? \n\nlike, if the fridge detects I'm opening it more often because I'm stressed, couldn't it signal the thermostat to change the temp to \"gauge\" my reaction or just to mess with me? it feels like once you start looking at how these things connect, it's not just a coincidence anymore.",
